<item>
            <title>[LU-2670] LNET routing to the same destination through multiple networks</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2670</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We would like to export multi-rail Lustre through routers to one destination network. It looks like it is not allowed in current implementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My lnet module option is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;routes=&quot;gni0 xxx.xxx.110.xxx@tcp0 xxx.xxx.111.xxx@tcp1&quot; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get this error:&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 5598:0:(router.c:399:lnet_check_routes()) Routes to gni via xxx.xxx.111.xxx@tcp1 and xxx.xxx.110.xxx@tcp not supported&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The manual states (p301): &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;It is an error to specify routes to the same destination with routers on different local networks.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It will be very great if this limitation can be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
